div.p:
I’m having lunch with Andy tomorrow. I already told him on the phone:
—The President has a long and deep interest in the matter, having personally inserted the reference to the deserts in his June 19 speech;The President said: “In a climate of peace, we here will do our full share to help with a solution for the refugees. We here will do our full share in support of regional cooperation. We here will do our share, and do more, to see that the peaceful promise of nuclear energy is applied to the critical problems of desalting water and helping to make the deserts bloom.” (Public Papers of the Presidents of the United States: Lyndon B. Johnson, 1967, Book I, p. 634)
—The Bunker mission made a good start;
—Our Water for Peace man is hard at work;
—We have galvanized the World Bank into planning in this field.
